1
00:00:00,867 --> 00:00:01,933
<i>- Sir Gio!
- Welcome back, Sir Gio!</i>

2
00:00:02,067 --> 00:00:03,200
<i> You're going back to Manila?</i>

3
00:00:03,333 --> 00:00:05,133
<i>I don't want you to be
in danger because of me.</i>

4
00:00:05,267 --> 00:00:07,600
<i>We won't let you disappear
from our lives.</i>

5
00:00:07,733 --> 00:00:09,767
This family will never separate.

6
00:00:10,933 --> 00:00:12,433
<i>It's impossible that what
happened had nothing to do</i>

7
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:13,867
with Dad and Uncle Mike's death.

8
00:00:13,967 --> 00:00:15,233
<i> But the man is dead.</i>

9
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:16,733
<i> I've killed him.</i>

10
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:18,600
<i> If what Roi says is true...</i>

11
00:00:18,767 --> 00:00:21,233
<i>They didn't kill each other.
There's someone else.</i>

12
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,633
<i> That person is still free...</i>

13
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:28,200
My siblings could be in danger.

14
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,433
What if I don't leave?

15
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,567
Ma, we already talked
about this, haven't we?

16
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:34,933
And Mom,

17
00:00:35,033 --> 00:00:36,667
this might help you, too.

18
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:38,933
Like, you originally planned.

19
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:43,233
But it's like... I feel like
I can't leave you anymore.

20
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,300
Mom, I have something for you.

21
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:46,300
Wow!

22
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,400
- It's beautiful!
- You'll be able to use this

23
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,433
when it's winter in Spain.

24
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:53,600
- It looks good on you.
- Thank you, thank you.

25
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:56,900
Mom, you're not going
to leave us.

26
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,933
We will not allow you
to not come back.

27
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:04,300
But of course, you can stay
as long as you like.

28
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,100
What if we just all go there?

29
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:09,333
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

30
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,167
Mom, we're not kids anymore

31
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:13,633
that you need to bring
with you everywhere.

32
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:15,967
Besides, Leon and I
need to manage

33
00:01:16,067 --> 00:01:18,200
the businesses that Dad left.

34
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:21,867
But you have to heal.

35
00:01:22,567 --> 00:01:24,967
After your dad's death,

36
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:28,133
you immediately took over
the hotel.

37
00:01:28,233 --> 00:01:30,367
- And the incident with Roi--
- Mom, Mom.

38
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:36,600
We promise,
we're going to be okay.

39
00:01:36,700 --> 00:01:37,667
Hmm?

40
00:01:37,833 --> 00:01:41,467
As long as we're together,
we're going to be fine.

41
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:43,833
[JADE] Plus...

42
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:47,400
You should put yourself
first now, Mom.

43
00:01:48,533 --> 00:01:52,233
You've been taking care of us
all your life.

44
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:53,967
Time to prioritize yourself now.

45
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:58,700
Besides, we're going to be
there. We will visit you.

46
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,833
And...

47
00:02:00,933 --> 00:02:03,333
I can go home whenever I want.

48
00:02:04,367 --> 00:02:07,167
Come here, you kids.

49
00:02:07,333 --> 00:02:08,833
[CHUCKLING]

50
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,033
- Mm.
- We'll miss you, Mom.

51
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:15,400
What good have
I done in the world

52
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:18,533
to have such loving children.

53
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:20,867
- [CHUCKLES]
- Your father raised you right.

54
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:24,400
Thank you for...

55
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:26,867
for understanding me.

56
00:02:26,967 --> 00:02:28,500
I love you so much.

57
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:32,500
[SMOOCHES] I love you, Ma.

58
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:33,433
Hmm...

59
00:02:35,533 --> 00:02:42,567
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:38,600
Sir, I'm glad you have
a strong case against Roi.

61
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:41,667
Mrs. Almazan's statement saying
that Roi was at the crime scene

62
00:03:41,833 --> 00:03:43,600
when the crime happened
was a huge help.

63
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:46,167
Almazans' lawyers are already
on the move

64
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:47,733
to file a murder case
against Roi.

65
00:03:47,867 --> 00:03:48,667
Two counts of murder.

66
00:03:48,867 --> 00:03:50,900
Our lawyers will also
coordinate with them

67
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:53,300
to file a case against Roi
for killing our father.

68
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:55,333
File all the applicable cases
against him.

69
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:56,700
Murder, kidnapping of Jade...

70
00:03:56,867 --> 00:03:59,500
He even harmed Aunt Frida
and Leon.

71
00:03:59,633 --> 00:04:01,700
Include what he did
to Kiko in his house.

72
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,967
That way, he'll be
in prison for life.

73
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:07,833
Ma'am, sir, thank you.

74
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:10,533
Thank you for helping us out
in Roi and Bong's case.

75
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,833
We're just doing our job.

76
00:04:13,967 --> 00:04:15,033
[MONETTE] Sir.

77
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:16,533
Here's the key for the pickup

78
00:04:16,667 --> 00:04:18,700
- and the speedboat's ready.
- Oh, thank you.

79
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:20,533
Looks like you're
going somewhere.

80
00:04:20,667 --> 00:04:23,133
You should ride with us.
We're going to the city.

81
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,967
But finish your coffee first.

82
00:04:30,267 --> 00:04:31,633
Hello, Papa.

83
00:04:31,767 --> 00:04:33,633
Are you surprised
that we are here?

84
00:04:34,433 --> 00:04:35,900
We're still complete, look.

85
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:38,300
Pa.

86
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:40,367
Roi is in jail.

87
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:42,833
The guy who killed you
and Uncle Fred.

88
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,967
I hope you and Uncle
are at peace now.

89
00:04:48,033 --> 00:04:49,667
Have a shot there from heaven.

90
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:54,367
I hope Papa can still see us.

91
00:04:55,167 --> 00:04:57,300
That we didn't sell the hotel,

92
00:04:57,433 --> 00:05:00,333
and the three of us
are managing it.

93
00:05:02,467 --> 00:05:04,333
Grandma said...

94
00:05:04,467 --> 00:05:05,933
that they're never truly gone.

95
00:05:07,367 --> 00:05:08,667
Just like Mama.

96
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,933
She still watches over me.

97
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:13,600
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

98
00:05:13,767 --> 00:05:16,067
I do hope Papa
can see us from up there.

99
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:19,433
He might give us some
advice about what to do.

100
00:05:21,267 --> 00:05:22,500
Advice about what?

101
00:05:23,633 --> 00:05:25,667
What we should do
with the Almazans.

102
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:29,933
I mean, yes, we worked together
on everything that happened.

103
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:30,933
But...

104
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:32,767
[SIGHS]

105
00:05:32,933 --> 00:05:34,867
Now that the truth
has come out...

106
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:38,767
It turns out that our fathers
didn't kill each other.

107
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:42,633
We were wrong
to judge each other.

108
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:45,467
But we can't go
back to the hotel

109
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:47,633
and act like everything's
okay now, right?

110
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,600
What?

111
00:05:48,733 --> 00:05:50,367
We're suddenly chummy now?

112
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:53,033
Didn't they say anything bad
about us?

113
00:05:54,267 --> 00:05:56,567
But we have to figure out a way
that won't affect things

114
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:58,600
because of our relationship.

115
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:01,400
So the hotel can thrive.

116
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:04,733
In other words...

117
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,600
We need to be
in good terms with them?

118
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:10,600
We need...

119
00:06:10,700 --> 00:06:13,267
to actually be friends
with them.

120
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:15,133
Just like Papa and Uncle Fred.

121
00:06:15,267 --> 00:06:20,400
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

122
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,300
Here's your key.

123
00:06:28,433 --> 00:06:30,400
Please assist her, Pamela.
Thank you.

124
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:32,833
Enjoy.

125
00:06:37,367 --> 00:06:38,733
You should be proud.

126
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,300
The number of
hotel guests increased

127
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:42,600
thanks to the music fest.

128
00:06:42,733 --> 00:06:44,200
[RAPHIE]
Do you have reservations?

129
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:45,800
Your project is a success.

130
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:51,133
- [RAPHIE] Your keys. Enjoy!
- [HOTEL GUEST] Thank you!

131
00:06:51,233 --> 00:06:52,833
How are you feeling?

132
00:06:55,733 --> 00:06:57,100
- Kiko mentioned--
- I'm okay.

133
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,600
How's Jade?

134
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,267
We told her
not to work for now

135
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,700
because we know that what
happened to her was traumatic.

136
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,000
The Bok guy.

137
00:07:11,467 --> 00:07:14,667
- [PHONE CHIMES]
- [RAPHIE] How sweet!

138
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:17,567
A guest booked our hotel
for a debut celebration!

139
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:20,233
- Birthday?
- Oh, I love that!

140
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:22,367
- What do we need?
- A lot of energy.

141
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,167
Is it a party?
I'll take care of it.

142
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:25,200
Go on, ask them.

143
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:26,567
[RAPHIE] Okay.

144
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,567
- [GIO] Debut date.
- [RAPHIE] I'm excited.

145
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:34,733
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

146
00:07:37,933 --> 00:07:39,067
Right?

147
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:44,500
Ah, excuse me.
Here's your drink, ma'am.

148
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,700
- Thank you.
- I'll get your main in a bit.

149
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,033
- Ah, okay.
- Thank you.

150
00:07:55,467 --> 00:07:56,433
[THUDS]

151
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,667
Sorry, I didn't see you.

152
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,067
- Are you okay?
- It's fine.

153
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,600
[RAPHIE] Sir, sir, sir!
I'll handle that.

154
00:08:02,567 --> 00:08:04,167
I'm really sorry.

155
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:05,433
- Raphie.
- [RAPHIE] Sir?

156
00:08:05,567 --> 00:08:06,767
Give our guest any drink
he wants.

157
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:08,100
- On the house.
- Okay.

158
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:09,567
Which is on the house?

159
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:14,033
Oh, the guest's drink spilled,
Sir Leon.

160
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,533
Justin?

161
00:08:16,633 --> 00:08:18,267
I already said I'm sorry.

162
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:19,667
I didn't mean it.

163
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,933
I'm sorry, sir.

164
00:08:22,067 --> 00:08:23,100
It's fine.

165
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:23,967
I'll go now.

166
00:08:28,167 --> 00:08:29,300
[CHESKA] A knife?

167
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:31,567
<i> Why does he have a knife?</i>

168
00:08:34,567 --> 00:08:35,967
Let's go, back to work.

169
00:08:38,167 --> 00:08:39,133
Justin.

170
00:08:39,300 --> 00:08:43,633
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:49,467
[FRIDA] I went here
to again personally apologize

172
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:51,033
for Roi's actions.

173
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:54,400
The lawyers are taking care
of everything.

174
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:58,100
It's okay.

175
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,200
[MARTIN STAMMERING]

176
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,167
I mean...

177
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:02,767
It's not okay that Papa died.

178
00:09:02,767 --> 00:09:05,367
However, you don't have
to apologize

179
00:09:05,367 --> 00:09:06,800
for your driver's actions.

180
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:08,933
My brother's right.

181
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:11,300
You are a victim, too.

182
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:17,500
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:18,733
A lot has changed.

184
00:09:19,367 --> 00:09:21,367
I remember
when you were all little,

185
00:09:21,367 --> 00:09:23,633
just running around here.

186
00:09:23,633 --> 00:09:25,800
Everyone was happy.
We didn't have problems.

187
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:29,800
They said you're going to leave?

188
00:09:30,867 --> 00:09:32,200
[FRIDA SIGHS]

189
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:35,433
That's one of the reasons
why I'm here now.

190
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:39,600
I hope that before I leave...

191
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:43,733
Our families could reconcile.

192
00:09:43,733 --> 00:09:48,867
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:09:48,867 --> 00:09:52,167
I know that with everything
that happened to us,

194
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:54,467
what I'm asking for
is not easy.

195
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:57,567
But...

196
00:09:57,567 --> 00:10:01,167
I'm sure this is what
your fathers would have wanted.

197
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:06,200
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

198
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:07,167
[KIKO SIGHS]

199
00:10:07,167 --> 00:10:10,233
That's also what my brothers
and I want.

200
00:10:10,733 --> 00:10:12,967
We just don't know
where to start.

201
00:10:13,867 --> 00:10:15,500
[MONETTE] This calls
for a team building!

202
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:17,700
[LUNA] Are you saying
something, Miss Monette?

203
00:10:18,533 --> 00:10:20,900
I think it's time to bring back

204
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:24,367
the annual Hotel 88
team building!

205
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,633
I love it!

206
00:10:26,867 --> 00:10:29,500
The team building will revive
the hearts of the employees

207
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:31,600
who are losing
their interest in work.

208
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,833
[SARI SIGHS]

209
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:34,500
If you say so.

210
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,867
You are in charge
of the logistics.

211
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:38,600
I've also spoken to Trixie,

212
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:42,300
and she knows a facilitator
who will help the organizers

213
00:10:42,300 --> 00:10:43,400
for the whole program.

214
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:45,600
[SARI] Okay, sir!

215
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,400
I'll also help Miss Trixie
on the things she needs to do.

216
00:10:48,933 --> 00:10:52,267
I also know of a possible venue!

217
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:54,500
Ohh! Go, Team Hotel 88!

218
00:10:55,267 --> 00:10:56,600
[MARTIN EXHALES DEEPLY]

219
00:10:57,867 --> 00:11:00,233
I'm entrusting you with that.

220
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:02,367
I don't want any foolishness,

221
00:11:02,367 --> 00:11:05,367
and I don't want a repeat
of the music fest,

222
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:07,367
where you brought
our siblings everywhere

223
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,633
without asking for permission.

224
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,600
Understood?

225
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:14,567
No foolishness,
you're entrusting this to me,

226
00:11:14,567 --> 00:11:17,433
and don't repeat what I did
at the music festival.

227
00:11:17,433 --> 00:11:20,900
Got it, copy all, check!
Copy, noted. On everything!

228
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:23,833
- [GASPS] And!
- And? There's more?

229
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:25,567
And have fun!

230
00:11:25,567 --> 00:11:27,667
I need to make sure
we all have fun.

231
00:11:27,667 --> 00:11:30,800
- Team building! Team building.
- Sari.

232
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,800
Team building, team building.

233
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:35,067
[SARI GIGGLES]

234
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:36,700
[SARI] Team building!

235
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,667
Jade!

236
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:43,667
- [JADE] Kiko! Hey.
- [KIKO CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

237
00:11:43,667 --> 00:11:45,867
Seems like we haven't talked
in a long time.

238
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:47,600
- Yeah.
- How are you?

239
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,033
Are you fine now?

240
00:11:49,033 --> 00:11:52,667
- You don't feel sick anymore?
- I'm fine now. Why?

241
00:11:52,667 --> 00:11:54,500
Ah, Jade.

242
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,633
- Come!
- [JADE] Where?

243
00:11:56,933 --> 00:11:58,833
[KIKO] Sir, can I borrow this?

244
00:11:58,833 --> 00:12:00,867
- Huh? But--
- Thank you.

245
00:12:00,867 --> 00:12:03,433
What is this?
Where-- Where are we going?

246
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:05,867
- We'll bike around!
- [JADE CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

247
00:12:05,867 --> 00:12:07,933
- Hop on.
- Do you know how to ride this?

248
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:09,933
- Of course!
- [JADE GIGGLES]

249
00:12:09,933 --> 00:12:11,100
[JADE] Hey.

250
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:17,467
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

251
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:20,467
[JADE] Kiko, wait.
Where are we going, anyway?

252
00:12:20,467 --> 00:12:22,967
- Just hold on!
- [GIGGLES] Drive slow, okay?

253
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:25,700
[JADE CHUCKLING]

254
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:27,100
- Woo!
- Woo!

255
00:12:28,533 --> 00:12:31,433
- [JADE] Woo! Woo!
- [KIKO] Woo!

256
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:34,633
Slow down, slow down!

257
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:40,633
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN CONTINUES]

258
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:41,600
[KIKO] Hold on.

259
00:12:42,367 --> 00:12:43,467
Hold on!

260
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:45,300
- [LAUGHTER]
- [JADE] Go slow!

261
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,400
[JADE LAUGHING] Kiko!
We're wobbling.

262
00:12:49,433 --> 00:12:51,367
- [KIKO] Woo!
- [JADE] Woo!

263
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:52,500
[LAUGHTER]

264
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:56,100
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN CONTINUES]

265
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:58,400
- [JADE] Woo!
- [KIKO] Wow!

266
00:13:02,933 --> 00:13:04,500
[KIKO] Just hold on.

267
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:07,700
- Hold on!
- [JADE LAUGHING] Go slowly!

268
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:08,833
[JADE GIGGLING]

269
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:09,800
[KIKO] Come.

270
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:11,867
Wait.

271
00:13:11,867 --> 00:13:13,400
- [KIKO GRUNTS]
- [JADE CHUCKLES]

272
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:15,867
[CHUCKLING]

273
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:18,033
[KIKO] What do you think?
You still okay?

274
00:13:18,033 --> 00:13:20,400
Is it okay that you suddenly
made me ride a bike?

275
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,433
Why? Didn't you have fun?

276
00:13:22,467 --> 00:13:25,400
Of course, I did! That's why...

277
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:26,767
- Matsa...
- Love.

278
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:28,533
Love.<i> Matsalove.</i> (Thank you)

279
00:13:28,533 --> 00:13:29,533
[JADE CHUCKLES]

280
00:13:31,033 --> 00:13:32,000
Jade.

281
00:13:33,700 --> 00:13:35,367
I'm sorry.

282
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:39,367
If I hadn't lost consciousness,
I could've saved you from Roi.

283
00:13:41,867 --> 00:13:43,767
I'm the one
who should apologize.

284
00:13:44,567 --> 00:13:45,900
For what?

285
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:50,033
If I didn't involve you
in my search for the truth,

286
00:13:50,033 --> 00:13:53,533
then you wouldn't have gotten
caught up in what Roi did.

287
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:55,433
Jade, it's honestly a good thing
you pulled me in this,

288
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:57,633
rather than you being all alone.

289
00:13:57,633 --> 00:14:00,467
I wish he would've taken me
instead of you.

290
00:14:00,467 --> 00:14:02,567
What? That can't be.

291
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:04,900
But it was really dangerous
what happened to you.

292
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,667
Even if you were
inside that drum,

293
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:07,800
it still would be dangerous.

294
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:11,733
That's nothing to me. It's fine.
Just not my friends.

295
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:12,767
Especially you.

296
00:14:12,767 --> 00:14:15,600
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

297
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:18,533
You're my best friend,
especially when we were young.

298
00:14:22,433 --> 00:14:23,400
Only when we were young?

299
00:14:24,567 --> 00:14:25,533
What about now?

300
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:29,033
Why?

301
00:14:29,767 --> 00:14:30,733
Is it still possible?

302
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:36,933
You said a lot has changed.

303
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:39,933
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

304
00:14:39,933 --> 00:14:41,600
Then propose first.

305
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,933
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY] Propose?

306
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:44,833
Yes.

307
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,567
[KIKO CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

308
00:14:48,967 --> 00:14:50,133
- [KIKO GRUNTS]
- [JADE GIGGLES]

309
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:53,967
Jade.

310
00:14:53,967 --> 00:15:00,800
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN CONTINUES]

311
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,067
Will you be my...

312
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,600
...best friend again?

313
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:06,533
[JADE CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

314
00:15:08,233 --> 00:15:10,100
Hmm...

315
00:15:13,167 --> 00:15:15,033
- Really?
- Yes.

316
00:15:15,033 --> 00:15:16,633
- You can't take that back.
- [JADE CHUCKLES]

317
00:15:16,633 --> 00:15:17,367
Whether in danger or not,

318
00:15:17,367 --> 00:15:19,200
no one's leaving
this friendship.

319
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,633
No one leaves.

320
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,800
Promise.

321
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:23,700
No one leaves.

322
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:25,900
- [HANDS CLAP]
- [JADE CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

323
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:32,867
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN CONTINUES]

324
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:35,767
No one's leaving.

325
00:15:40,233 --> 00:15:42,633
Ah. Let's go! Let's leave.

326
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:45,667
- [SMACKS]
- I thought no one's leaving?

327
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:47,233
We're leaving right away?

328
00:15:47,233 --> 00:15:50,000
It's true! We're leaving,
we're going home.

329
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,600
- Don't you want to?
- Fine, fine. Let's go.

330
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:55,067
- Am I driving the bike?
- Sure, if you can.

331
00:15:55,067 --> 00:15:56,633
[JADE CHUCKLING]

332
00:15:57,333 --> 00:15:58,533
- [JADE] Come on.
- [KIKO] Wait.

333
00:15:59,067 --> 00:16:00,233
[JADE] You should drive instead.

334
00:16:00,233 --> 00:16:02,033
- [KIKO] Excuse me...
- [JADE] I think you're heavy.

335
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:04,267
- [KIKO] I'm heavy?
- [JADE] You should drive.

336
00:16:04,267 --> 00:16:05,533
Come on.

337
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:15,633
- [KIKO]<i> Let's go!
</i>- [JADE CHUCKLING]

338
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:18,033
- [KIKO]<i> Come on.
</i>- [JADE] Can you even drive?

339
00:16:18,033 --> 00:16:20,233
- [KIKO]<i> Of course!
</i>- [JADE GIGGLING]

340
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:27,200
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

341
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:35,233
[PHONE RINGING]

342
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:43,433
[PHONE RINGING]

343
00:16:46,567 --> 00:16:48,433
Bud, Jade's calling.

344
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:51,733
Edward.

345
00:16:53,767 --> 00:16:55,300
Edward, aren't you gonna
answer it?

346
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:57,200
Dad, I'm busy. Just let it be.

347
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:01,767
Alright. Whatever you say.

348
00:17:01,767 --> 00:17:03,267
Anyway, um...

349
00:17:04,133 --> 00:17:05,767
Join me for dinner
when you're done.

350
00:17:05,767 --> 00:17:07,100
[EDWARD] Okay.

351
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:14,067
[PHONE RINGING CONTINUES]

352
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:18,500
Is Sir Edward not answering
your calls?

353
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:21,767
Yeah. He might still be
at the meeting.

354
00:17:21,767 --> 00:17:23,833
But don't worry. I'll talk
to him for the venue

355
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:25,367
- of our team building.
- [SQUEALS]

356
00:17:25,367 --> 00:17:27,200
Thank you, Ms. Jade! [SIGHS]

357
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:29,267
The resort that Sir Edward owns
is the only one that satisfies

358
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:31,467
the location requirements
of the facilitator.

359
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:33,367
If we don't give it our all,

360
00:17:33,367 --> 00:17:35,500
we might not be able
to secure it. [LAUGHS]

361
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,833
Are you the organizer
of the event?

362
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:39,367
Ms. Trixie is the one

363
00:17:39,367 --> 00:17:41,133
coordinating
with the facilitator.

364
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:44,833
Cheska volunteered
to help out as well.

365
00:17:45,367 --> 00:17:47,267
So you'll be able
to join us, huh?

366
00:17:47,267 --> 00:17:48,267
[GIGGLES]

367
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,567
Yes I will, Ms. Jade.

368
00:17:49,567 --> 00:17:51,733
I just really need to secure
this venue

369
00:17:51,733 --> 00:17:54,167
then we'll be able to proceed
with the team building!

370
00:17:54,167 --> 00:17:56,400
- [CHUCKLING]
- Consider it done.

371
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:58,400
You're such an angel, Ms. Jade!

372
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:00,233
I'll have your wings cut off

373
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:01,867
so you'll never go back
to heaven.

374
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:04,633
The world needs angels like you.

375
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:05,567
[BOTH GIGGLING]

376
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:07,167
- I'll go then, Ms. Jade.
- See you, Sari.

377
00:18:07,167 --> 00:18:08,400
Thank you!

378
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:15,400
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

379
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,367
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

380
00:18:16,367 --> 00:18:18,300
- [JADE]<i> Where are you?
</i>- [PHONE CHIMES]

381
00:18:23,433 --> 00:18:26,567
[PLEASANT MUSIC PLAYING]

382
00:18:26,567 --> 00:18:27,600
[JADE] Edward!

383
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:29,533
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

384
00:18:29,533 --> 00:18:30,567
[JADE] Ah.

385
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,633
- Edward.
- What are you doing here?

386
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:36,267
Can I talk to you?

387
00:18:36,267 --> 00:18:39,400
Uh... You weren't answering
my calls so...

388
00:18:40,767 --> 00:18:41,900
I'm busy.

389
00:18:42,733 --> 00:18:44,133
What is it about?

390
00:18:45,367 --> 00:18:46,400
Um...

391
00:18:46,933 --> 00:18:49,267
Luna was requesting
if it's possible

392
00:18:49,267 --> 00:18:51,667
to hold our team building
at Mystic Sports.

393
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,833
Can you tell your associates
to reserve it to us?

394
00:18:56,967 --> 00:18:58,333
That's it?

395
00:18:59,533 --> 00:19:00,767
Uh...

396
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:04,767
Lu-- Luna said that you are
invited to join us!

397
00:19:04,767 --> 00:19:06,800
You're part
of the promotions anyway

398
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:09,200
and because of the success
of the music festival too.

399
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,467
You'll join us, right?

400
00:19:11,467 --> 00:19:14,800
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

401
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,233
Will...

402
00:19:17,867 --> 00:19:19,367
Will Kiko be there too?

403
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,600
Uh...

404
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:24,467
Mm-hmm.

405
00:19:24,467 --> 00:19:26,600
He'll be coming
along with his siblings.

406
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:29,600
All the core staff
of Hotel 88 will come.

407
00:19:30,633 --> 00:19:33,267
Okay. Is that all?
'Cause I still...

408
00:19:33,267 --> 00:19:34,633
I still got things to do.

409
00:19:34,933 --> 00:19:36,633
Edward, wait.

410
00:19:38,967 --> 00:19:41,967
I still haven't
thanked you properly.

411
00:19:44,633 --> 00:19:46,667
Thank you for saving me.

412
00:19:46,667 --> 00:19:48,833
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

413
00:19:48,833 --> 00:19:50,500
I'll make it up to you
next time.

414
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:51,633
Promise.

415
00:19:52,267 --> 00:19:53,400
Next time?

416
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,300
Can't you do it all the time?

417
00:19:56,633 --> 00:19:57,933
[LAUGHS IN DISBELIEF]

418
00:19:57,933 --> 00:19:59,500
[LAUGHING] What do you mean?

419
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,333
Why are you laughing?

420
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,667
I thought you'll make it
up to me.

421
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:03,933
You can't laugh.

422
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:05,667
Sorry.

423
00:20:06,267 --> 00:20:07,833
You want to make it
up to me, right?

424
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:10,933
I have three wishes.

425
00:20:12,367 --> 00:20:14,967
Okay, sir. Three wishes?

426
00:20:15,933 --> 00:20:17,867
What are they, sir?

427
00:20:17,867 --> 00:20:19,500
I'll think about it.

428
00:20:20,967 --> 00:20:24,333
If you don't tell them
to me right now I might...

429
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,667
I might change my mind.

430
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:29,800
[LAUGHS]

431
00:20:32,867 --> 00:20:34,667
Just like how
you changed your mind

432
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:35,800
during prom?

433
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:41,900
[BITTER MUSIC PLAYING]

434
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:42,867
Huh?

435
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,400
Edward...

436
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,667
It's alright, Jade.

437
00:20:47,733 --> 00:20:50,567
I'm already used
to your broken promises.

438
00:20:50,567 --> 00:20:57,600
[BITTER MUSIC CONTINUES]

439
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:09,533
[FRIDA] Just give me an update.

440
00:21:09,567 --> 00:21:10,867
Always.

441
00:21:11,433 --> 00:21:14,700
And Luna, you can take it easy
every now and then.

442
00:21:14,700 --> 00:21:16,433
I'll do my best to do so, Ma.

443
00:21:16,433 --> 00:21:17,833
[LAUGHING]

444
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:19,700
Justin, please be a good boy.

445
00:21:19,700 --> 00:21:21,600
Don't make me worry, alright?

446
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:24,633
And call me if you need
someone to talk to.

447
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:27,433
I will always be
your good boy, Mom.

448
00:21:27,433 --> 00:21:29,300
- [FRIDA CHUCKLES]
- Bye bye.

449
00:21:29,567 --> 00:21:30,567
Bye.

450
00:21:31,733 --> 00:21:32,733
Jade.

451
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,833
Take care of your heart.

452
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:37,600
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

453
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,733
Take care, Mom. Alright?

454
00:21:39,733 --> 00:21:40,833
Yes.

455
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:41,900
[JADE LAUGHS]

456
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,633
I love you all so much.

457
00:21:44,433 --> 00:21:46,967
I'll miss you all
but I'll be back soon.

458
00:21:46,967 --> 00:21:48,100
Can I get a hug?

459
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:50,600
[LAUGHTER]

460
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:51,700
[JADE] Group hug!

461
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:53,400
[ALL GIGGLING] Mhm!

462
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,433
[FRIDA BREATHES DEEPLY]

463
00:21:54,433 --> 00:21:55,733
[FRIDA] I have to go.

464
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:59,467
- Bye, Mom.
- I'll see you soon!

465
00:21:59,467 --> 00:22:00,633
- [GIGGLES]
- Bye, Mom!

466
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:01,900
Bye!

467
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:05,067
Tell them that I'll send Mom
and Aunt Yayo to the airport

468
00:22:05,067 --> 00:22:07,300
so go on ahead
to the team building.

469
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:08,433
[JADE, LUNA] Okay, Leon.

470
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:09,900
Be careful.

471
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:11,033
Bye, Mom!

472
00:22:11,033 --> 00:22:12,500
We love you!

473
00:22:14,433 --> 00:22:16,333
[VAN DOOR SLIDES CLOSE]

474
00:22:16,967 --> 00:22:19,133
[CAR ENGINE STARTING]

475
00:22:19,133 --> 00:22:26,300
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

476
00:22:27,833 --> 00:22:29,800
[VAN DOOR SLIDING OPEN]

477
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:33,767
[STAFF, SARI] Mystical day!
Welcome to Mystic Sports!

478
00:22:34,933 --> 00:22:37,633
[RAPHIE] So this is what
being welcomed feels like!

479
00:22:37,633 --> 00:22:41,467
[INDISTINCT EXCITED CHATTERING]

480
00:22:41,467 --> 00:22:43,800
[JEEP ENGINE REVVING]

481
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:44,967
[CHESKA] I'll bring these.

482
00:22:44,967 --> 00:22:46,833
- [RAPHIE] Let me handle it!
- [CHESKA] It's okay!

483
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:49,433
[PLEASANT MUSIC PLAYING]

484
00:22:49,467 --> 00:22:50,500
[HANDLEBAR STRETCHES]

485
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:51,567
[JEEP DOORS OPEN]

486
00:22:54,667 --> 00:22:55,800
[JEEP DOORS CLOSE]

487
00:23:03,967 --> 00:23:07,367
[STAFF, SARI] Mystical day!
Welcome to Mystic Sports.

488
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:14,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

489
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:18,467
[CHIMING, CLINKING]

490
00:23:18,633 --> 00:23:25,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

491
00:23:37,333 --> 00:23:38,267
[LEON] Soliman?

492
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,667
"Meeting with Mr. Soliman:
Cafe Lumi in Belina."

493
00:23:40,833 --> 00:23:42,200
[LEON] Who is that?

494
00:23:44,333 --> 00:23:48,133
<i>Dad didn't mention
he had a new business partner.</i>

495
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:54,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

496
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:55,933
[CAMERA CLICKS]

497
00:23:56,067 --> 00:24:03,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

498
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:08,167
[LEON]<i> Who did Dad meet
</i> one week before he died?

499
00:24:08,333 --> 00:24:13,667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

500
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:15,133
[HENRI] Sandro Soliman?

501
00:24:16,767 --> 00:24:18,467
Yes, sir.

502
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,467
My father told me that...

503
00:24:20,567 --> 00:24:22,900
he's working on a
new project on Solara Island.

504
00:24:23,033 --> 00:24:25,167
So I'm here to look for him.

505
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:27,333
A project on Solara Island?

506
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:30,500
I'm not aware of
any construction there.

507
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,167
What kind of project was it?

508
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,233
He didn't mention it to me.

509
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:38,600
Shouldn't he have told you that?

510
00:24:40,133 --> 00:24:43,233
Papa always travels for work.

511
00:24:43,367 --> 00:24:44,500
Most of the time,

512
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,567
he doesn't get to tell me where.

513
00:24:47,867 --> 00:24:49,233
But, sir,

514
00:24:50,733 --> 00:24:53,067
no matter where
Papa ends up,

515
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:55,833
he always lets me know
he's okay.

516
00:24:55,933 --> 00:24:58,167
So now that I can't reach him,

517
00:24:59,133 --> 00:25:00,767
I'm scared that...

518
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:04,233
I'm scared that something
might have happened to him.

519
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:09,367
Are you scared that
your father might be dead?

520
00:25:12,067 --> 00:25:13,533
Yes, sir.

521
00:25:13,633 --> 00:25:17,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

522
00:25:17,467 --> 00:25:18,533
[HENRI SIGHS]

523
00:25:19,433 --> 00:25:20,400
Alright, come on.

524
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:27,600
Dela Paz will assist you.

525
00:25:27,733 --> 00:25:31,067
We'll contact you as soon as
we get a lead on your father.

526
00:25:31,233 --> 00:25:35,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

527
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:39,200
Did your father mention
a place before he went missing?

528
00:25:39,367 --> 00:25:42,667
He had a meeting
in the town of Belina.

529
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:44,767
Oh.

530
00:25:44,933 --> 00:25:46,833
That's a different town.

531
00:25:47,133 --> 00:25:48,633
Did you ask around there?

532
00:25:48,767 --> 00:25:49,633
Not yet, ma'am.

533
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:53,100
A new restaurant just
opened there, Cafe Lumi.

534
00:25:53,267 --> 00:25:55,900
Maybe that's the project
your father worked on.

535
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,567
Go check it out.

536
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:00,800
Sign here.

537
00:26:00,933 --> 00:26:07,967
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

538
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,833
<i> This is treasure hunting!</i>

539
00:26:15,967 --> 00:26:17,933
<i>- Are you ready?!
- Yes!</i>

540
00:26:18,033 --> 00:26:19,933
<i>We will divide you
into two teams.</i>

541
00:26:20,033 --> 00:26:22,933
<i>- Get ready! Get set! Go!
- Yes!</i>

542
00:26:23,033 --> 00:26:28,700
[ENGINE REVVING]

543
00:26:28,833 --> 00:26:30,267
<i> Sir! Sir! Aah!</i>

544
00:26:30,367 --> 00:26:32,300
<i>Get it off!
Get it off!</i>

545
00:26:32,467 --> 00:26:33,700
<i> Focus, Sari.</i>

546
00:26:33,833 --> 00:26:36,000
<i> I need...</i>

547
00:26:36,133 --> 00:26:37,867
<i>- Help.
- Jade.</i>

548
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:42,033
<i>- Move!
- [SCREAMS]</i>

